IMPORT fs

' plan-59-E Phase 2 — the SAFETY NET, landed before either ownership rule is
' removed.
'
' plan-59-E deletes TYPE_RESOURCE_INVALIDATE_NOT_OWNER and
' TYPE_RESOURCE_ELEMENT_NOT_OWNER. `res.md` §8 says that change "loses static
' use-after-close"; the sub-plan's Non-goals narrow that — straight-line
' `close(a); use(a)` must STILL be a compile error, because it is caught by a
' DIFFERENT rule (TYPE_USE_AFTER_MOVE, 2-203-0055).
'
' The danger this fixture exists to catch is that a rule which stops firing makes
' negative tests pass VACUOUSLY. A silent loss of protection looks exactly like
' success in a green run. So each function below is a case that fires today and
' must keep firing; the golden records one error per case, and losing any line is
' the regression.
'
' The three cases are the ones §14.9's algorithm actually promises. See this
' sub-plan's Correction C4 for the fourth case that does NOT fire (a close in a
' loop body observed across the back edge) — that is specified behaviour, not a
' gap this fixture should assert.

' 1. Straight-line: the simplest and most important case.
FUNC straightLine(p AS String) AS Nothing
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile(p)
  fs::close(f)
  LET s AS String = fs::readAll(f)
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

' 2. Across a branch join: closed on only ONE arm. §14.9 unions "moved on some
'    fall-through path" into the outer set, so the use after the join is rejected
'    exactly as a definite move would be.
FUNC branchJoin(p AS String, cond AS Boolean) AS Nothing
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile(p)
  IF cond THEN
    fs::close(f)
  END IF
  LET s AS String = fs::readAll(f)
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

' 3. After a loop whose body closed it: the body's moves union back into the
'    outer set on fall-through, so the use after END WHILE is rejected.
FUNC afterLoop(p AS String) AS Nothing
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile(p)
  MUT n AS Integer = 0
  WHILE n < 2
    fs::close(f)
    n = n + 1
  END WHILE
  LET s AS String = fs::readAll(f)
  RETURN NOTHING
END FUNC

FUNC main AS Integer
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
